Asia Interactive Media Inc.: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 22, 2017 7:57 PM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of Asia Interactive Media Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Asia Interactive Media Inc. does not have significant operations. It intends to merge with, engage in a capital stock exchange with, purchase all or substantially all of the assets of, or engage in any other similar business combination with one or more operating businesses. The company was formerly known as Black Gardenia Corp. and changed its name to Asia Interactive Media Inc. in March 2007. Asia Interactive Media Inc. was founded in 2000 and is based in Central, Hong Kong.


Bank of China TowerLevel 301 Garden RoadCentral,  Hong KongFounded in 2000



Phone: 852 9836 2643








Key Executives for Asia Interactive Media Inc.




Mr. Ken Ng


      	CEO, President, CFO, Principal Accounting Officer, Secretary, Treasurer and Director
      


Age: 51
        




Compensation as of Fiscal Year 2017. 

Asia Interactive Media Inc. Key Developments

Asia Interactive Inc. Announces Auditors Changes
Nov 4 16
On November 2, 2016, Asia Interactive Media Inc. announced that George Stewart, CPA, the company’s independent registered public accountant, has resigned his engagement with the company effective November 2, 2016. The decision to resign was entirely due to Stewart’s desire to transition towards retirement and was accepted by the sole director of the company on November 2, 2016. On November 2, 2016, the sole director approved the appointment of Fruci & Associates II, PLLC as the company’s new independent registered public accountant.


Asia Interactive Media Inc. announced delayed 10-Q filing
Aug 16 16
On 08/16/2016, Asia Interactive Media Inc. announced that they will be unable to file their next 10-Q by the deadline required by the SEC.


Asia Interactive Media Inc. announced delayed annual 10-K filing
Mar 31 16
On 03/31/2016, Asia Interactive Media Inc. announced that they will be unable to file their next 10-K by the deadline required by the SEC.


