Suzanne WilsonDeputy General Counsel, The Walt Disney Company Chief Counsel









 

Suzanne Wilson 

Deputy General Counsel, The Walt Disney Company Chief CounselWilson joined the Walt Disney Company as Deputy General Counsel in 2011 overseeing the Company’s attorneys responsible for worldwide legal oversight of copyright, trademark, patent, consumer products licensing, online and console games, online properties, and antipiracy enforcement matters. As the head lawyer for Disney Consumer Products and Interactive Media, Wilson provides strategic legal advice to DCPI's executive management team and manages the group that provides legal support to the various business operations within the interactive media segment of DCPI.
Prior to joining Disney in 2011, Wilson was a partner at the law firm Arnold & Porter LLP. Wilson holds a Bachelor of Arts degree in Economics from the University of California at Berkeley, and a Juris Doctor, magna cum laude, from Harvard Law School.




